      • filterFoundResolvers

        public void filterFoundResolvers(java.util.List<ImportResolver> importResolvers,
                                 java.io.File file)
        Provides for a capability by which a set of resolvers can be trimmed by a found sorter implementation. This provides great power to the sorter to force itself to be used over a group of other resolvers. Plugin implementers should take great caution in using this only when it is guaranteed to be the correct behavior.
        Parameters:
        importResolvers - the list of import resolvers that to filter. The modification are made directly to the importResolvers list.
        file - the file that is being considered for the resolvers.

        Invoked after the file has been successfully copied or moved to initiate import.

        The default implementation returns immediately.

        dst - The file resulting from the copy or move.
        flags - Enum set of flags that the user wishes to use to modify sort behavior.

      • getDisplayableName

        public abstract java.lang.String getDisplayableName()
        Get a human readable string that can be displayed to the user so that they can differentiate between different sorter implementations. This string MUST be unique to a sorter, and any duplicates will likely be removed before the user gets a chance to see them.
        Returns:
        Unique (by class, not instance), human readable name for this sorter.
